NAME
    App::ssl4curl - Download and setup Mozilla certificates for curl SSL/TLS
    access

USAGE
    Initialize from command line as root or use sudo or if you have
    local::lib set up execute as standard user.
                "sudo ssl4curl -i"

    then add to ~/.bashrc to check/download and setup certificates using
    Mozilla::CA module on start of every session.
                "export `ssl4curl -p`"

                or

    you can execute "ssl4curl" on command line instead to check/download
    certificates and list export string. Then you can add output string into
    your ~/.bashrc instead in which case check/download will be skiped on
    start of session.
                "ssl4curl"

    Print this pod
                "ssl4curl -h"

